From the search, cultural competence in healthcare refers to the ability of providers to understand and respect the cultural beliefs, practices, and needs of patients from diverse backgrounds. This includes being aware of one's own cultural biases and assumptions, as well as educating oneself about different cultures.

Culturally competent care can lead to better patient satisfaction, adherence to treatment plans, and overall health outcomes.

